paris-1-skillsKnowledge.def: Access to an improved water source is currently defined as the percentage of the population that can obtain at least 20 liters per person per day from an “improved” source that is within one kilometer of the user’s dwelling. Improved water sources include household connection, public standpipe, borehole, protected well or spring, and rainwater collection, but do not include water provided through vendors, tanker trucks, unprotected wells, unprotected springs, and bottled water.
paris-1-skillsKnowledge.source: World Health Organization and United Nations Children's Fund, Joint Measurement Programme (JMP)
paris-1-skillsKnowledge.dataset: World Health Organization and United Nations Children's Fund, Joint Measurement Programme (JMP)

paris-10-skillsKnowledge.def: Prevalence of underweight children under-five years of age, also known as prevalence of child malnutrition (weight for age), is the percentage of children under-five whose weight for age is less than minus two standard deviations from the median for the international reference population ages 0 to 59 months.
paris-10-skillsKnowledge.source: World Health Organization (WHO) , Global Database on Child Growth and Malnutrition
paris-10-skillsKnowledge.dataset: World Health Organization (WHO) , Global Database on Child Growth and Malnutrition

paris-11-skillsKnowledge.def: Under-five mortality rate is the probability that a newborn baby will die before reaching age five, if subject to current age-specific mortality rates. The probability is expressed as a rate per 1,000. The indicator measures child survival.
paris-11-skillsKnowledge.source: UNICEF, WHO, World Bank, UN DESA, UNDP
paris-11-skillsKnowledge.dataset: UNICEF, WHO, World Bank, UN DESA, UNDP

paris-111-skillsKnowledge.def: Quality of source data (composite of indicators).

paris-112-skillsKnowledge.def: Use of the Special Data Dissemination Standard. The Special Data Dissemination Standard (SDDS) was established by the IMF for member countries to guide them in providing their economic and financial data to the public.

paris-125-skillsKnowledge.def: Reporting of education data to UNESCO. UNESCO Institute of Statistics compiles data on education based on official responses to surveys and from reports provided by education authorities in each country.

paris-131-skillsKnowledge.def: Quality of vital registration data and system coverage. Vital registration systems record the occurrence and characteristics of vital events pertaining to the population and serve as a main source of vital statistics.
paris-131-skillsKnowledge.source: United Nations Department of Economic and Social Information and Policy Analysis, Statistics Division. Population and Vital Statistics Report.
paris-131-skillsKnowledge.dataset: United Nations Department of Economic and Social Information and Policy Analysis, Statistics Division. Population and Vital Statistics Report.

paris-135-skillsKnowledge.def: This indicator measures whether the national statistical legislation complies with United Nations Fundamental Principles of Statistics (SDG 17.18.2)

paris-143-skillsKnowledge.def: This indicator measures whether it exists an official country-operated, dedicated online portal for reporting SDG progress, detailed either in the government webpage or NSO website.

paris-15-skillsKnowledge.def: The CPI is a statistical estimate constructed using the prices of a sample of representative items whose prices are collected periodically. The annual percentage change in a CPI is used as a measure of inflation.
paris-15-skillsKnowledge.source: IMF: International Financial Statistics (IFS) - Country notes
paris-15-skillsKnowledge.dataset: IMF: International Financial Statistics (IFS) - Country notes

paris-155-skillsKnowledge.def: Coverage Element 1 for ODIN data coverage score. It measures the extent to which representative indicators within each data category are disaggregated categorically and geographically.
paris-155-skillsKnowledge.source: Open Data Watch - Open Data Inventory
paris-155-skillsKnowledge.dataset: Open Data Watch - Open Data Inventory

paris-156-skillsKnowledge.def: Coverage Element 2 for ODIN data coverage score. It measures whether data are available in a data category over the last five years.
paris-156-skillsKnowledge.source: Open Data Watch - Open Data Inventory
paris-156-skillsKnowledge.dataset: Open Data Watch - Open Data Inventory

paris-157-skillsKnowledge.def: Coverage Element 3 for ODIN data coverage score. It measures whether data are available in a data category over the last ten years.
paris-157-skillsKnowledge.source: Open Data Watch - Open Data Inventory
paris-157-skillsKnowledge.dataset: Open Data Watch - Open Data Inventory

paris-158-skillsKnowledge.def: Coverage Element 4 for ODIN data coverage score. It measures whether data are available at the first administrative level.
paris-158-skillsKnowledge.source: Open Data Watch - Open Data Inventory
paris-158-skillsKnowledge.dataset: Open Data Watch - Open Data Inventory

paris-159-skillsKnowledge.def: Coverage Element 5 for ODIN data coverage score. It measures whether data are available at the second administrative level.
paris-159-skillsKnowledge.source: Open Data Watch - Open Data Inventory
paris-159-skillsKnowledge.dataset: Open Data Watch - Open Data Inventory

paris-160-skillsKnowledge.def: Openness Element 1 for ODIN data openness score. It measures whether data are available in a machine readable format such as XLS, XLSX, CSV, and JSON.
paris-160-skillsKnowledge.source: Open Data Watch - Open Data Inventory
paris-160-skillsKnowledge.dataset: Open Data Watch - Open Data Inventory

paris-161-skillsKnowledge.def: Openness Element 2 for ODIN data openness score. It measures whether data are available in a non-proprietary  format such as XLSX, CSV, DOCX, XML, HTML and JSON.
paris-161-skillsKnowledge.source: Open Data Watch - Open Data Inventory
paris-161-skillsKnowledge.dataset: Open Data Watch - Open Data Inventory

paris-162-skillsKnowledge.def: Openness Element 3 for ODIN data openness score. It measures whether data are available with three different download options: bulk download, API, and user-select options.
paris-162-skillsKnowledge.source: Open Data Watch - Open Data Inventory
paris-162-skillsKnowledge.dataset: Open Data Watch - Open Data Inventory

paris-163-skillsKnowledge.def: Openness Element 4 for ODIN data openness score. It measures whether metadata are made available.
paris-163-skillsKnowledge.source: Open Data Watch - Open Data Inventory
paris-163-skillsKnowledge.dataset: Open Data Watch - Open Data Inventory

paris-164-skillsKnowledge.def: Openness Element 5 for ODIN data openness score. It measures whether data are available with an open terms of use.
paris-164-skillsKnowledge.source: Open Data Watch - Open Data Inventory
paris-164-skillsKnowledge.dataset: Open Data Watch - Open Data Inventory

paris-29-skillsKnowledge.def: The principal sources of external debt statistics are reports submitted to the World Bank through its Debtor Reporting System by reporting countries. Data quality and coverage vary among countries and from year to year. The reporting status shows, for the latest series, whether data were used as reported (actual), data were preliminary and included an element of staff estimation (preliminary), or data are staff estimates (estimate).
paris-29-skillsKnowledge.source: International Debt Statistics (for low- and middle-income countries)
paris-29-skillsKnowledge.dataset: International Debt Statistics (for low- and middle-income countries)

paris-32-skillsKnowledge.def: This indicator captures whether countries subscribe to enhanced General Data Dissemination System (e-GDDS).

paris-36-skillsKnowledge.def: This indicator is defined as the ratio of the gross enrollment rate of girls to boys in primary and secondary education levels in both public and private schools.
paris-36-skillsKnowledge.source: UNESCO Institute for Statistics: Table 5: Enrolment ratios by ISCED level
paris-36-skillsKnowledge.dataset: UNESCO Institute for Statistics: Table 5: Enrolment ratios by ISCED level

paris-40-skillsKnowledge.def: Health surveys collect information on various aspects of health of populations, such as health expenditure, access, utilization, and outcomes.

paris-41-skillsKnowledge.def: HIV prevalence at any given age is the difference between the cumulative numbers of people who have become affected with HIV up to this age and the number who died, expressed as a percentage of the total number alive at this age. The basis of measuring infection is the incidence of HIV among people aged 15-49.

paris-43-skillsKnowledge.def: Amount of IMF reports on the observance of standards and codes (ROCs).

paris-44-skillsKnowledge.def: Import and export price indexes measure changes in the price of goods and services in international trade. They are used to deflate the value of imports and exports.
paris-44-skillsKnowledge.source: IMF: International Financial Statistics (IFS). Series 74, 75, or/and 76.
paris-44-skillsKnowledge.dataset: IMF: International Financial Statistics (IFS). Series 74, 75, or/and 76.

paris-46-skillsKnowledge.def: Proportion of population below US$1.25 a day is the percentage of the population living on less than $1.25 a day at 2005 international prices.
paris-46-skillsKnowledge.source: World Bank, Development Research Group, PovacalNet
paris-46-skillsKnowledge.dataset: World Bank, Development Research Group, PovacalNet

paris-47-skillsKnowledge.def: Industrial production index measures changes in industrial production and is widely used for the observation and analysis of the current economic activity.

paris-5-skillsKnowledge.def: Agricultural censuses collect information on agricultural activities, such as agricultural land use, employment and production, and provide basic structural data and sampling frames for agricultural surveys.

paris-50-skillsKnowledge.def: This indicator measures whether the NSO webpage has a language-accessible portal, providing information at least in another language in addition to the national one.

paris-57-skillsKnowledge.def: Births attended by skilled health staff are the percentage of deliveries attended by personnel trained to give the necessary supervision, care, and advice to women during pregnancy, labor, and the postpartum period, to conduct deliveries on their own, and to care for the newborns.
paris-57-skillsKnowledge.source: UNICEF: State of the World's Children.
paris-57-skillsKnowledge.dataset: UNICEF: State of the World's Children.

paris-62-skillsKnowledge.def: National accounts base year is the year used as the base period for constant price calculations in the country's national accounts.
paris-62-skillsKnowledge.source: World Bank: World Development Indicator (Primary Data Documentation)
paris-62-skillsKnowledge.dataset: World Bank: World Development Indicator (Primary Data Documentation)

paris-64-skillsKnowledge.def: WHO and UNICEF collect and review data available on national immunization coverage. Then estimates on the level of immunization coverage are made by using officially reported data, survey results, scientific literature, and by taking account of potential biases and consultation with local experts. The gap between the international estimates and the government official estimates therefore suggests that the estimation method adopted by the country differs from the internationally recommended practice.

paris-7-skillsKnowledge.def: The Balance of Payments Manual serves as an international standard for the compilation of balance of payments statistics.
paris-7-skillsKnowledge.source: IMF: Balance of Payment Statistics yearbook (BPS)
paris-7-skillsKnowledge.dataset: IMF: Balance of Payment Statistics yearbook (BPS)

paris-77-skillsKnowledge.def: This indicator reports the link to the country NSO website.

paris-78-skillsKnowledge.def: ODIN score of data coverage. Data coverage is assessed against five elements of coverage. Coverage Element 1: Indicator Coverage and Disaggregation;Coverage Element 2: Data Availability for Last 5 Years;Coverage Element 3: Data Availability for Last 10 Years;Coverage Element 4: First Administrative Level;Coverage Element 5: Second Administrative Level
paris-78-skillsKnowledge.source: Open Data Watch - Open Data Inventory
paris-78-skillsKnowledge.dataset: Open Data Watch - Open Data Inventory

paris-79-skillsKnowledge.def: ODIN score on coverage of economic statistics data.
paris-79-skillsKnowledge.source: Open Data Watch - Open Data Inventory
paris-79-skillsKnowledge.dataset: Open Data Watch - Open Data Inventory

paris-81-skillsKnowledge.source: Open Data Watch - Open Data Inventory
paris-81-skillsKnowledge.dataset: Open Data Watch - Open Data Inventory

paris-82-skillsKnowledge.def: ODIN score on coverage of environmental statistics data.
paris-82-skillsKnowledge.source: Open Data Watch - Open Data Inventory
paris-82-skillsKnowledge.dataset: Open Data Watch - Open Data Inventory

paris-83-skillsKnowledge.def: ODIN score on openness of environmental statistics data.
paris-83-skillsKnowledge.source: Open Data Watch - Open Data Inventory
paris-83-skillsKnowledge.dataset: Open Data Watch - Open Data Inventory

paris-84-skillsKnowledge.source: Open Data Watch - Open Data Inventory
paris-84-skillsKnowledge.dataset: Open Data Watch - Open Data Inventory

paris-85-skillsKnowledge.def: ODIN score of data openness. Data openness is assessed against five elements of openness.
paris-85-skillsKnowledge.source: Open Data Watch - Open Data Inventory
paris-85-skillsKnowledge.dataset: Open Data Watch - Open Data Inventory

paris-86-skillsKnowledge.def: ODIN scores are summarized along both dimensions of the ODIN assessment: by categories, and by elements. Categories: social statistics, economic statistics, and environmental statistics. Elements: coverage and openness.
paris-86-skillsKnowledge.source: Open Data Watch - Open Data Inventory
paris-86-skillsKnowledge.dataset: Open Data Watch - Open Data Inventory

paris-87-skillsKnowledge.def: ODIN score on coverage of social statistics data.
paris-87-skillsKnowledge.source: Open Data Watch - Open Data Inventory
paris-87-skillsKnowledge.dataset: Open Data Watch - Open Data Inventory

paris-88-skillsKnowledge.def: ODIN score on openness of social statistics data.
paris-88-skillsKnowledge.source: Open Data Watch - Open Data Inventory
paris-88-skillsKnowledge.dataset: Open Data Watch - Open Data Inventory

paris-89-skillsKnowledge.def:
ODIN score on social statistics. Social Statistics include:
1. Population and Vital Statistics
2. Education Facilities
3. Education Outcomes
4. Health Facilities
5. Health Outcomes
6. Reproductive Health
7. Gender Statistics
8. Crime and Justice Statistics
9. Poverty Statistics.
paris-89-skillsKnowledge.source: Open Data Watch - Open Data Inventory
paris-89-skillsKnowledge.dataset: Open Data Watch - Open Data Inventory

paris-9-skillsKnowledge.def: The proportion of one-year-old children immunized against measles is the proportion of children aged one who received one dose of measles vaccine. A child is considered adequately immunized against measles after receiving one dose of vaccine.

paris-93-skillsKnowledge.def: Quality of statistical production periodicity (composite of indicators).

paris-95-skillsKnowledge.def: Population censuses collect data on the size, distribution and composition of population and information on a broad range of social and economic characteristics of the population.
paris-95-skillsKnowledge.source: United Nations Statistical Division (UNSD), 2010 World Population and Housing Censuses Programme
paris-95-skillsKnowledge.dataset: United Nations Statistical Division (UNSD), 2010 World Population and Housing Censuses Programme

paris-96-skillsKnowledge.def: Poverty surveys collect data on household income, consumption and expenditure, including income in kind. They typically include income, expenditure, and consumption surveys, household budget surveys, Integrated Surveys, Living Standard Measuring Surveys, and other poverty related surveys. It is recommended that poverty surveys be conducted at least every 3 to 5 years.

paris-98-skillsKnowledge.def: This indicator measures whether official statements on statistical indicators are issued to journalists at least on a quarterly basis.
